<?xml version="1.0"?>
<rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#"
         xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#"
         xmlns:rdfs="http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#"
         xmlns:owl="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#"
         xml:base="http://www.stiima.cnr.it/RientraReturns"
         xmlns="http://www.stiima.cnr.it/RientraReturns#"
         xmlns:swrl="http://www.w3.org/2003/11/swrl#"
         xmlns:SkAb="http://www.stiima.cnr.it/SkAb#"
         xmlns:ICF-="http://www.stiima.cnr.it/ICF-exc-coreset#"
         xmlns:JobL="http://www.stiima.cnr.it/JobList#"
         xmlns:JobD="http://www.stiima.cnr.it/JobDescription#"
         xmlns:Rien="http://www.stiima.cnr.it/RientraOnt3#"
         xmlns:Rien2="http://www.stiima.cnr.it/RientraOnt3Merged#"
         xmlns:Rien3="http://www.stiima.cnr.it/RientraHC#"
         xmlns:FOAF="http://www.stiima.cnr.it/FOAF-excerpt#">

<owl:Ontology rdf:about="http://www.stiima.cnr.it/RientraReturns">
  <rdfs:comment rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">A box importing:
- JobList
- SkAb for the full description and translation of Jobs with ICF.

Developed for "Rientr@" ontology by STIIMA-CNR.</rdfs:comment>
  <rdfs:comment rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Added professions:
- Dancers
- Travel guides
- Receptionists and Information Clerks
- Insurance policy processing Clerks
- Insurance Claims Clerks
- Billing, cost and rate Clerks
- Bookkeeping, Accounting, and Auditing Clerks

On February 2022.</rdfs:comment>
  <rdfs:comment rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">An excerpt od Friend Of a Friend (FOAF) ontology for people's description.
Developed for "Rientr@" ontology by STIIMA-CNR.

Full FOAF: http://xmlns.com/foaf/spec/</rdfs:comment>
  <rdfs:comment rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Based on Standard Occupation Classification (2016 version) available on O*NET web site: https://www.onetonline.org/</rdfs:comment>
  <rdfs:comment rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Common Box for Person description importing:
- Health Condition (RientraHC)
- FOAF (FOAF-excerpt)
- ICF (excerpt and core sets)</rdfs:comment>
  <rdfs:comment rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Developed on: 29 November 2021.
Latest revision: 30 april 2024.
Version: 3.1.</rdfs:comment>
  <rdfs:comment rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Excerpt of ICF developend for the "Rientr@" project by STIIMA-CNR.
It contains the classes composing:
- Traumatic Brain Injury comprehensive core set
- Spinal Cord Injury (Long Term/Chronic) comprehensive core set
- Stroke comprehensive core set
- Vocational Rehabilitation comprehensive core set
- Codes description, Inclusion and Exclusions added

Full ICF ontology: https://www.bioportal.bioontology.org/ontologies/ICF (updated May 2012).</rdfs:comment>
  <rdfs:comment rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Excerpt of O*NET "Skills" and "Abilities" for descriptions of jobs.
Developed for "Rientr@" ontology by STIIMA-CNR.</rdfs:comment>
  <rdfs:comment rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Health Condition Ontology for modelling wheelchair users' health conditions.
Developed for "Rientr@" ontology by STIIMA-CNR.</rdfs:comment>
  <rdfs:comment rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">List of jobs to be matched with the wheelchair users.
Developed for "Rientr@" ontology by STIIMA-CNR.</rdfs:comment>
  <rdfs:comment rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Revised on 08 June 2020.
Translation of O*NET in ICF deeply revised (elimination of the "translator" individuals and classes):
- SWRL "matrix" revision: specific scores for Skills and Abilities according to the new version of the matrix (Risk factor);
- 8 new SWRL rules deployed.</rdfs:comment>
  <rdfs:comment rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Rientra Ontology importing:

1. Person ontology (Common Box), which imports:
      a) Health Conditions (RientraHC)
      b) FOAF (FOAF excerpt)
      c) ICF (excerpt and core sets)

2. Job Description (Common Box), which imports:
      d) Job List
      e) Skills and Abilities (SkAb)</rdfs:comment>
</owl:Ontology>

<owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://www.stiima.cnr.it/JobDescription#isImportantFor">
  <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="http://www.stiima.cnr.it/SkAb#Abilities"/>
  <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="http://www.stiima.cnr.it/SkAb#Skills"/>
  <rdfs:range rdf:resource="http://www.stiima.cnr.it/JobList#Job"/>
</owl:ObjectProperty>

